author: Justin Harp
title: TV show ratings: Jane the Virgin dips in its Monday return - The Big Bang Theory Cult
text: Jane the Virgin was down in its return to The CW on Monday (October 12), according to Nielsen figures.Jane fell two-tenths of a point from last year's opening at 9pm, garnering 0.4 (1.06m). At 8pm, Crazy Ex-Girlfriend received 0.3 (0.90m). © The CW / Greg Gayne The Big Bang Theory topped the night overall with 3.9 (14.96m) at 8pm on CBS, before Life in Pieces earned 1.8 (7.84m) at 8.30pm and Scorpion took 1.7 (9.40m) at 9pm.NCIS: Los Angeles averaged 1.1 (8.45m) at 10pm on CBS.NBC won the key 18-49 demographic on Monday with 3.0.The Voice and Blindspot held steady on NBC, appealing to 3.3 (11.96m) at 8pm and 2.5 (8.45m) at 9pm. © NBC Universal Dancing with the Stars attracted 1.7 (11.64m) at 8pm on ABC, followed by Castle reaching 1.1 (6.78m) at 10pm.Fox's Gotham reeled in 1.5 (4.17m) at 8pm. At 9pm, Minority Report garnered 0.7 (2.05m).
